signed-ingress change): beyond your per-scenario observables, assert the FREE oracles this class of change always affords — drive them from the negative/edge inputs you already wrote, never open-ended fuzzing (no spec-driven generator; the 2-cycle budget is your only fuse). HTTP oracle: any 5xx during a lane is a crash-class FAIL even if no scenario asserted it; any response whose shape violates the changed response TYPE is a contract bug — derive the expected shape from the type, not the code; if there's no OpenAPI spec for the surface, do not assert "undocumented status"; add a DELETE-then-GET=404 metamorphic check only if the route is genuinely resource-CRUD. Streaming oracle (if the surface streams): over the frames collected, assert every data frame before the terminal marker parses cleanly (a parse failure is a FAIL, never silently dropped), exactly ONE terminal marker with nothing after it, the terminal-only completion field set correctly, and that concatenated content deltas reassemble the full message. Signature oracle (any signed-ingress route the diff touches): a forged or replayed signature must be REJECTED with the documented code — this is invisible to the 5xx/shape oracle (a forged signature accepted with 200 is neither a 5xx nor a shape bug); the edge gate's auth+malformed dimensions cover MISSING/MALFORMED, so additionally add a WRONG-KEY (well-formed signature, wrong secret) and a REPLAYED (resend a valid signature in-window) negative case. {{E2E_HARNESS}} names the project's actual route/type/test-file surfaces for each oracle, if applicable — a project with no signed-ingress or no streaming surface skips that oracle.
